frus:attachment.p:
The U.S. Delegation should indicate to the Soviets that either side would have the right to withdraw from the agreement unless adequate revisions can be negotiated, and in the absence of such revisions the United States must be prepared to exercise its right of withdrawal from the agreement. The following are illustrative grounds for revision or withdrawal from the agreement: (1)
if the capability of any third country reaches the point where either party to the agreement believes that its security is threatened; (2)
if either side believes that extraordinary events have undermined the stability of the agreement; (3)
if there is evidence of evasion of the terms of the agreement; (4)
if either party takes action which interferes significantly with the other’s verification capability or otherwise adversely affects the capability of the other party to verify compliance with the agreement.
